2124.subject: CHHS
2124.descrlong: This course introduces students to community building, local development strategies and regional economic issues (especially focused on small and rural communities).  Students will study the economic conditions that strengthen community opportunities for employment growth.  Topics include community history and capacity for growth and job creation, the role of community-based organizations and public economic development agencies.
